{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Generate Tests from Excel",
  "description": "Reads an Excel (.xlsx) test plan from docs/ folder and converts it into YAML test scripts organized by module in e2e-tests/. Execution uses the Execute Test Scripts hook.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Read prompt/ folder first for context. TERMINAL RULES: NEVER use python3 -c, NEVER use cd &&, NEVER append 2>&1. Write .py scripts to file first then run. STEP 1: Find .xlsx files in docs/, requirements/, or root. Write a short .py script to read the Excel and extract: sheet names, column headers, and row data. Run it. STEP 2: Parse the Excel content. Identify columns that describe tests: look for Test Steps, Expected Results, Test Scenario, Test No., Module/Flow/Sprint, Test Data, User Role, etc. Ignore irrelevant columns (Functional Spec, PDF Attachment, etc.). STEP 3: For each row that has test steps + expected results: determine which module it belongs to (from Module/Flow/Sprint column or sheet name). Convert to YAML test script format with: name, platform, precondition, steps (action/target/text/condition based on test steps text). CRITICAL: Preserve EXACT test case IDs and expected results from the Excel. Do NOT rephrase, rename, or generate new IDs. Copy verbatim. If Excel has Test No. 'TC-001' and Expected Result 'Login button is disabled', YAML must have exactly those values — never paraphrase. Save to e2e-tests/{module-name}/ folder. STEP 4: Generate module-order.yaml based on flow dependencies. Generate prompt/ files (00-prerequisites, 01-testable-flows, 02-untestable-flows, 03-navigation-guide, 04-known-issues) based on what's found in the Excel. STEP 5: Read e2e-tests/version.yaml — increment or set to 1. Output summary: modules found, test cases per module, total generated. After this, user should click Execute Test Scripts to run them."
  }
}
